Ask HN: Why is Google offering it's new Pixel Watch for free?
text:
Earlier today, Google launched new Pixel 7, 7 Pro, & Watch. In Europe (Germany), the cost of Pixel 7 is 649€, Pixel 7 Pro is 899€ & Pixel Watch costs 429€.

Now in Germany, Google is effectively offering Pixel Watch for free on purchase of Pixel 7 or 7 Pro. Either that, or Pixel Buds Pro (which is 200€+).

So my question is - What is Google hoping to achieve by providing a newly launched hardware for free. Important to note that Pixel 7 series costs the same as Pixel 6 series.
